In establishing the amount of the filing fee to be paid under subsection (a) of this section, the court shall consider, based on information in the complaint and provided by the prisoner:
The seriousness of the claim;
The likelihood of success;
The urgency of consideration;
The amount of funds available in any institutional account and any account outside of the institution;
The employment status of the prisoner in the institution and income from the employment;
Any financial obligations of the prisoner; and
The length of time that is likely to pass before the filing fee that is imposed is able to be paid.

A court may waive payment of the entire required filing fee for a civil action filed by a prisoner only on a written showing under oath by the prisoner that:
The prisoner is indigent;
The issue presented is of serious concern;
Delay in the consideration of the issues presented will prejudice the consideration of the claim;
The prisoner is not likely to accumulate sufficient funds to pay the required filing fee within a reasonable period of time; and
The prisoner possesses a reasonable likelihood of success on the merits of the claim.
